notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.
The second quire is missing entirely, as well as a few leaves from the third quire.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Alfasi's commentary on the treatises of Seder Nashim and Neziḳin, with a marginal commentary mostly taken from Rashi and with references to other sources.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 ; ruled lines: 36; written lines: 36; Hard-point ruling and pricking visible. Hair-side and flesh-side of leaves distinguishable. Extensive marginal notes. Inital words written in large characters.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Italian semi-cursive script of the 14th to 15th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine title: 'Isaac ben Jacob Al Fasi. Halakhoth. Seder Nashim u-Nezikin. Hebrew & Aramaic. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,075.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Giuseppe Almanzi (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 180: his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for £1,000 through Asher & Co., Berlin dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153): inscribed, folio [201v].
